38. Nf1 {I don't think blitz games should be overanalysed but to have a look
at a few interesting positions is always fun. Here we see the top see in big
trouble. d6 is about to fall and realizing just that, Black decided to sac a
piece.} Bxg4 39. Qxd6 ({And Black gets rewarded!} 39. fxg4 Nxe4 40. Qa4 $1 Nxd2
41. Qc2+ {would have forced Bassem's resignation... but that is blitz!}) 39...
Nc8 (39... Bh3+ 40. Kf2 Bxf1 {wins material, but seconds were ticking away...})
40. Qxc5 Bh3+ 41. Kg1 Bxf1 42. Bxg5 Qg2# {Mate! The Algerian GM had a shaky
first part of the Blitz section but, faster than a tumbler toy, he readjusted
his position in the standings after a raging 5/5 in the final rounds. A second
place for Mohamed in the combined standings and a prize of US$ 4,000.} 0-1

