Angolan IM, David Silva. He finished right behind Bassem, which brought him to
a 4th place in the combined standings. In this example though, he felt the
danger blowing in his neck.} 21... Qd8 {A natural defensive move, especially
for a Blitz encounter, but objectively not the strongest response.} ({Weirdly
enough, the 'unnatural'} 21... O-O {running straight into White's attack after}
22. h5 Qd8 23. Qh6 {is the safest path to victory, as Black has the very
beautiful} g5 $1 $19) 22. bxa4 Qxg5+ 23. hxg5 Bxa2 {the beginning of the end.}
({Once again,} 23... O-O {would have kept Black's slight advantage.}) 24. Rb7
Bd5 25. Rc7 Bb3 26. Bb5 Rd8 27. Bd2 c4 28. Ba5 h5 29. Bxc4 Bxa4 30. Bxe6 {
